param

Class ParamResult

  • java.lang.Object
    • param.ParamResult

  • public class ParamResult
extends java.lang.Object
    Stores the result of a ParamModelChecker run (a RegionValues object) as well as additional information (ModelBuilder, FunctionFactory) that is needed to test the actual result against an expected result (test mode).

      • getSimpleResult

        public java.lang.Object getSimpleResult(Type propertyType)
                                 throws PrismException
        If ParamModelChecker ran in exact mode (no parametric constants), the result will consist of a single region and a single value instead of a function.
        This method returns this single value (either a Boolean or a BigRational).
        Parameters:
        propertyType - the type of the checked property
        Returns:
        Boolean/BigRational result (for the initial state)
        Throws:
        PrismException - if there are multiple regions or the value is a function
